Create Tables 

DDL (Data Definition Language) - creates the data and defines it

table design:
- can contain max 30 chars (no blanks)
- must begin with letter
- can conatain numbers, underscore, and #
- must be unique
- no reserved words can be used (SELECT, FROM, etc) 

datatype: 
4 dominate types
VARCHAR2(n) where n = length of characters
CHAR(n)

VARCHAR is elastic, can adjsut with the length of value
CHAR is static, cannot adjust with the length of value

NUMBER(p,s)
DATE 

CREATE TABLE tablename (columnname datatype [DEFAULT value] [, columnname2 datatype
] );

Metadata:
data about your data. customers in your table is your data, how many customers 
are in your database is metadata.


